725506f-a.title: Queens: 59th Drive - 63rd Street
725506f-a.text:
59th Drive (along line of fence), east of 63rd Street (left not
seen), showing in the background a part of the former Alden Sampson
and Sons oil cloth factory. Nost of it was demolished prior to 1929.
Alden Sampson and Sons were owners from 1873-1896, and one Linnbergard
owned it in 1924.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
